OL,3,CSummerland 50th Anniversary: What
OL,4,Chappened and why does it matter?
OL,6,FAfter realising the fire doors were
OL,7,Flocked, everyone ran in the same
OL,8,Fdirection, causing a crush at the main
OL,9,Fentrance.
OL,11,FThe fire then caught on a material
OL,12,Fcalled Oroglas which was used to build
OL,13,Fthe roof.
OL,15,FThis caused burning Oroglas to then
OL,16,Fdrip down onto people trying to escape.
OL,18,FThe flames first became visible inside
OL,19,Fthe building at around 8:00pm and the
OL,20,Ffirst fire engine was on the scene by
OL,21,F8:07pm.
