OL,6,FA memorial site was unveiled in 2013
OL,7,Ffor the 40th anniversary of the
OL,8,Fdisaster, including two pillars
OL,9,Flisting the 50 names of those who died
OL,10,Fas a result of the fire.
OL,12,FThis is now formally known as the Kaye
OL,13,FMemorial Gardens, where Douglas
OL,14,FCouncil hold their annual remembrance
OL,15,Fservice.
OL,17,FSurvivors, families of victims and
OL,18,Fother officials travelled to the Isle
OL,19,Fof Man for the 50th anniversary.
